,
voice calls
and
chats
that can be accessed through the Halodoc Platform with the following conditions:
Users can contact the Service Provider when the Service Provider
is online
.
User can cancel the
Chat
Feature with the Doctor that has been appointed with the  Service  Provider  maximum  45  (forty  five)  minutes  before  the schedule starts.
Service Provider may cancel the
Chat
Feature with Doctor maximum 30 (thirty) minutes before the schedule appointed by User.
If you do not show up at the scheduled time, you agree that the funds you have paid are non-refundable.
If  the  Service  Provider  is  not  present  at  the  schedule  that  you  have specified within a maximum of 10 (ten) minutes after the scheduled time, we will refund your funds in accordance with the applicable procedures.
We will  send  notifications  regarding  the appointment schedule that you specify via
push notification
on your electronic device. To be able to receive
push notifications
that We send, You must activate the
push notification
.
You acknowledge and agree that the
Chat
with Doctor Feature does not replace examination and treatment with a doctor in general or face-to-face.
We will  make  every effort to  have the  Service  Providers  listed  on  the Halodoc Platform respond to your queries as soon as possible. However, We do not recommend that you use the Halodoc Platform for emergency medical conditions. Users with emergency conditions, We recommend that you find the nearest health facility or call 119.
Halodoc  Services are neither coercive nor binding. The decision to use Halodoc  Services  through  Halodoc  Platform  is  entirely  yours.  Halodoc Platform is only a facilitator of interaction between Service Providers and Users.
You understand that you  need to  provide  information and describe your symptoms or physical complaints completely, clearly and accurately when having a conversation with the Service Provider.
If necessary, the Service Provider (doctor) will provide a referral for
offline
consultation to conduct further consultation regarding your complaint.
You have full control over how your health information is shared. You may share your User Health History with other Service Providers (doctors) to continue  treatment.  By  consenting  and  sharing  this   information,  You authorize other Service Providers (doctors) to use and/or view Your User Health History. You may contact Us further to exercise your right to manage and/or revoke your consent.
Furthermore, by you agreeing and/or sharing User Health History, you also understand and agree to release all legal claims and/or compensation to Halodoc for the dissemination and/or use of User Health History by other Service Providers (doctors).
