Terms of Transaction of Chat with Doctor Feature
Users will be charged a certain amount to be able to use the
Chat
with Doctor Feature.
If the User requires a video call or voice call with the Service Provider, the User needs to inform the relevant Service Provider in advance and will depend on the availability of each Service Provider at the time of contact.
Halodoc  balance will be deducted directly from the conversation screen when it appears on the phone screen and when the User is connected to the Service Provider. One conversation session with the Service Provider starts from 30 (thirty) minutes up to 1 (one) hour from the conversation session starts or until the User or Service User ends the conversation session.
When contacting a doctor via conversation, the User may send the Service Provider images relating to the User's medical condition in PNG, JPG, and Bitmap formats.
Once the session is over, the Service Provider can provide Doctor's Notes and Medication Recommendations.
The Service Provider (doctor) can follow up with the User to check the User's health condition after the session.
Transactions cannot be canceled after the session ends or is completed.
Halodoc may block or cancel the User's account if there is any misuse of the Chat Feature on the User's account.
The Service Provider (doctor) can provide a doctor referral as a reference.
The   accuracy   and   precision   of the Service Provider in Drug Recommendations will depend on the information provided by the User. Any contents and/or statements in conversations conducted by the User with the Service Provider using the video call, voice call
, chat,
Doctor's Note, and/or Drug Recommendation features, on the Halodoc Platform.
Health Store Features
The Health Store Feature is managed by PT Mensa Medika Investama (“
PT MMI
”). The Health Store Feature may be connected to applications and/or other platforms owned by third parties that collaborate with Halodoc and are appointed by Halodoc to deliver orders to you. You are expected to read and understand all the terms determined by the third party before using the third party’s services.
The Health Store Feature cannot be used for the delivery of medicines classified as narcotics and psychotropics and restricted medicines classified as certain drugs in accordance with the laws of the Republic of Indonesia.
Halodoc is not responsible for any material or immaterial losses, claims, or demands arising from negligence and/or mistakes of the Service Provider and/or any third party, including but not limited to the provision of prescriptions that do not comply with the laws and regulations of the Republic of Indonesia, prescription errors, delivery errors, prescription misuse, mistakes and/or other negligence of the Service Provider in relation to the use of the Health Store Feature. For the avoidance of doubt, Halodoc only provides a platform that connects Service Providers and Users.
Transaction Terms for the Health Store Feature
Users may be charged for the Product price, Handling Fee (if any), Service Fee, Delivery Fee, and other fees as stated on the Halodoc Platform at the “Payment Summary” page. Users understand that there is a price range within the Halodoc Platform, which may cause the prices listed on the Halodoc Platform to differ from the prices when purchasing the Products offline.
Users can choose between regular delivery or instant delivery services under the following conditions:
Regular Delivery:
The delivery time for regular service of the Products ordered by the User is between 1 - 4 days from the time the Products are picked up by the delivery service from the Service Provider (pharmacy).
Instant Economy Delivery:
The delivery time for Instant Economy service of the Products ordered by the User is generally 180 (one hundred and eighty) minutes from the time the Products are picked up by the delivery service from the Service Provider (pharmacy).
Instant Delivery:
The delivery time for instant service of the Products ordered by the User is generally 60 (sixty) minutes from the time the Products are picked up by the delivery service from the Service Provider (pharmacy).
However, the delivery process will depend on the selected delivery type and the conditions at the time the order is sent. Orders may arrive faster or later than estimated, depending on conditions including but not limited to distance, courier availability from the delivery service, weather conditions, and/or traffic conditions.
Product availability varies depending on the stock owned by Halodoc’s partner Service Providers. If the Products ordered by the User come from multiple Service Providers, the User may choose to have multiple deliveries, in which case the delivery fee will be borne by the User.
Each purchase of Products in the Health Store Feature that uses Health Insurance/Health Benefits is subject to the policy of each Health Insurance/Health Benefit provider.
If the order has been picked up by Halodoc’s partner Service Provider and/or is in the process of delivery by the courier, the User cannot cancel the order.
Users understand and agree that if there are additional fees beyond the Delivery Fee arising in connection with the delivery of the Products, including but not limited to parking fees and building entry fees requested by the User, then the User is required to bear these fees, and the delivery courier has the right to request reimbursement of these fees directly from the User by providing supporting proof (parking receipt).
The transaction value that Users can conduct on the Health Store Feature for a single transaction is a minimum of Rp10,000 (ten thousand Rupiah) and a maximum of Rp5,000,000 (five million Rupiah).
Specifically for Products with a doctor’s prescription, Users are required to attach a document in the form of a photo of the doctor’s prescription first and upload it through the ‘Upload a Prescription’ feature on the Halodoc Platform for order verification with the Service Provider (pharmacy).
If Users use the ‘Upload a Prescription’ feature, Users are required to submit the original prescription that was used as the basis for purchasing the Product through Halodoc to be handed over to the Service Provider (pharmacy) receiving the purchase.
Prescriptions made by the Service Provider can only be used
once
and cannot be reused.
By using the Health Store Feature, Users agree that the selection of the Service Provider (pharmacy) can be made independently through the Official Store Feature or based on recommendations from the Halodoc system.
Homecare Features
The Homecare Service Feature allows Users to conduct laboratory tests (both package and individual tests), receive vitamin boosters, vaccinations, as well as consultations and physical examinations at a location of their choice without having to visit a laboratory or healthcare facility in person.
Users can choose the type of laboratory tests available in the Homecare Service feature according to referrals from the Service Provider.
The availability of test packages and schedules selected by the User will be adjusted according to the schedule of each of Halodoc’s partner laboratories.
Vaccination services will be carried out by registered Service Providers. Before vaccination, Users will undergo a written screening via WhatsApp and a physical screening by the Service Provider at the User's location.
Users ordering the COVID & Flu Antigen Swab Test Service in the Individual Lab Test menu:
Understand that their test results will be kept confidential and can only be accessed by the User, authorized healthcare personnel, and/or government institutions handling the COVID-19 pandemic. COVID-19 test results will only be issued by laboratories or hospitals that collaborate with Halodoc. Additionally, Users agree to receive an explanation of the examination procedure and approve the actions to be taken regarding the COVID-19 test by healthcare personnel from Halodoc’s partners.
Acknowledge and agree that, for the User's convenience, the COVID-19 Test results will be provided in digital format and uploaded to the User’s account for viewing (“
COVID-19 Test Results
”).
Acknowledge and agree that the COVID-19 Test Results will be entered into the Halodoc system using security measures that comply with the standard regulations of the Republic of Indonesia.
Transaction Terms for the Homecare Feature
For the implementation of the Homecare Service Feature, Halodoc collaborates with a number of affiliated clinic personnel (“
Affiliated Clinic Personnel
”), where the execution and laboratory test results are conducted and issued by the Affiliated Clinic Personnel.
Users are required to fill in the Homecare Service Feature order data completely and accurately. By ordering the Homecare Service Feature, Users are deemed to have agreed to the details of the order made through the Halodoc Platform and are willing to be contacted by the relevant personnel.
In addition to ordering for themselves, Users can place orders for others (“
Third-Party Orders
”). Users guarantee that they have obtained the necessary consent for the execution of Third-Party Orders related to the Homecare Service Feature, where Third-Party Orders are subject to every part of these Terms and Conditions.
Homecare services are conducted based on the general procedures of the Affiliated Clinic Personnel. By registering for the Homecare Service, Users are deemed to have agreed to comply with all general procedures set by the Affiliated Clinic Personnel.
Users located in the Greater Jakarta area (Jabodetabek) who place Homecare Service orders amounting to more than Rp250,000 (two hundred and fifty thousand Rupiah) will not be charged transportation fees for Affiliated Clinic Personnel to travel to the User’s designated location. Outside of this provision, transportation fees will be charged according to the applicable Terms and Conditions.
Payment methods for the Homecare Service can only be made through the payment methods available on the Halodoc Platform at the time of ordering.
If the Affiliated Clinic Personnel has already departed for the User’s designated location, the User cannot cancel the order. Cancellations can only be made at the latest 24 (twenty-four) hours before the scheduled appointment.
If the Affiliated Clinic Personnel is unable to collect the User’s sample within 30 (thirty) minutes after arriving at the designated location due to factors beyond their control, including but not limited to the User’s health condition at the time of the visit and other factors from the User that make sample collection impossible, the User agrees that the order cannot be canceled, is considered completed, and the payment made by the User is non-refundable for any reason.
Users can reschedule Homecare Lab Services by: (i) Rescheduling via the Halodoc Platform no later than 24 (twenty-four) hours before the appointment; or (ii) Rescheduling through the Homecare Service administrator. If the User does not provide a replacement schedule to the Homecare Lab Service administrator within 3 (three) calendar days after the initial appointment date, the User agrees that the order is considered completed and the payment is non-refundable.
Users acknowledge and agree that for their convenience, Homecare Service examination results will be provided in digital format and uploaded to the User’s account on the Halodoc Platform (“
Lab Test Results
”).
Lab Test Results will be delivered by the Affiliated Clinic Personnel to the User within the timeframe specified on the Halodoc Platform.
By using the Homecare Service Feature, Users acknowledge and agree that the Lab Test Results will be entered into the Halodoc system using security measures that comply with standard regulations in the Republic of Indonesia. In the case of Third-Party Orders, the Lab Test Results for that Third-Party Order will still be uploaded to the Halodoc account of the User who placed the order. Users acknowledge and hereby consent that they may access materials related to the Lab Test Results when necessary, and that Halodoc may use abstracts and/or metadata from the Lab Test Results for the development of the Halodoc Platform. Furthermore, Users also agree that the Lab Test Results constitute Personal Data and will be subject to all provisions in the Privacy Policy.
Users can request a printed copy of the results from the Affiliated Clinic Personnel who served them. Any costs incurred for the request and/or delivery of a printed copy of the Lab Test Results will be borne by the User.
The entire content of the Lab Test Results is the full responsibility of the Affiliated Clinic Personnel.
Users can download the Lab Test Results through the Halodoc Platform. The security of the downloaded Lab Test Results is the responsibility of the User.
Users understand and are responsible for any actions, negligence, and/or omissions related to the processing or dissemination of information from the Lab Test Results of Third-Party Orders.
Users acknowledge that in cases of force majeure or if a Lab Test Result requires further confirmation, there is a risk of delays in sample collection, delivery, and/or issuance of the Lab Test Results by the Affiliated Clinic Personnel. Halodoc is not obligated to provide compensation to the User in any form for such delays.
All information, procedures, and operations related to the Homecare Service Feature available on the Halodoc Platform are the responsibility of each Affiliated Clinic Personnel. Halodoc is not responsible for any interactions between Users and Affiliated Clinic Personnel, nor for any procedures and/or actions related to the Homecare Service Feature on the Halodoc Platform.
