6.2. Special Services
Haloskin Feature: This feature is a digital skin clinic offering services including but not limited to personalized acne treatment packages, curated and formulated by Our team of dermatologists for Users. To receive treatment, You will go through a pre-assessment process, where the photo You upload will be analyzed using artificial intelligence (AI) services. This AI service helps provide treatment recommendations best suited to Your skin condition.
Sexual Health Feature: The Sexual Health Feature facilitates Users to consult with Service Providers (doctors) via video call, voice call, or chat accessible through the Halodoc Platform to discuss their health. This feature also provides lab test services and the purchase of medications through the Health Store feature. Any medical recommendations, prescriptions, and diagnoses provided by the Service Provider (doctor) are the medical authority of the respective Service Provider (doctor).
Mental Health Feature: The Mental Health Feature includes a chatbot service that helps Users understand their mental condition. If necessary, Users can further consult with Service Providers (mental health professionals such as psychiatrists or psychologists) registered on the Halodoc Platform.
Animal Health Feature: The Animal Health Feature facilitates Users to consult with Service Providers (veterinarians) via video call, voice call, or chat accessible through the Halodoc Platform to discuss their pet’s health. Any medical recommendations, prescriptions, and diagnoses provided by the Service Provider (veterinarian) are the medical authority of the respective Service Provider (veterinarian).
Cancer Care Feature: The Cancer Care Feature facilitates Users to consult with Service Providers (doctors) via video call, voice call, or chat accessible through the Halodoc Platform to discuss their health. This feature also provides lab test services and the purchase of medications through the Health Store feature. Any medical recommendations, prescriptions, and diagnoses provided by the Service Provider (doctor) are the medical authority of the respective Service Provider (doctor).
Bidan
Services Feature:
This feature facilitates partner Midwives as Service Providers to interact with You through consultation services via the Application in accordance with the authority and obligations of the Midwife.
Transaction Terms for the
Bidan
Services Feature:
Users will be charged a certain Service Fee to use the Chat with Midwife Feature.
The Halodoc balance will be deducted directly once the chat screen appears on the phone and once the User is connected to the Service Provider. One chat session with the Service Provider (midwife) lasts 30 (thirty) minutes to 1 (one) hour from the start of the session or until the User or the Service Provider ends the session.
When contacting the Service Provider via chat, Users may send images related to their condition in PNG, JPG, and Bitmap formats.
Transactions cannot be canceled after the chat session with the Service Provider has ended or been completed.
Halodoc may block or cancel transactions if there is any misuse of the Chat with Midwife Feature.
Heart Care Feature: The Heart Health Feature facilitates Users to consult with Service Providers (doctors) via video call, voice call, or chat accessible through the Halodoc Platform to discuss their health. This feature also provides lab test services and the purchase of medications through the Health Store feature. Any medical recommendations, prescriptions, and diagnoses provided by the Service Provider (doctor) are the medical authority of the respective Service Provider (doctor).
Diabetes Care Feature: The Diabetes Care Feature facilitates Users to consult with Service Providers (doctors) via video call, voice call, or chat accessible through the Halodoc Platform to discuss their health. This feature also provides blood sugar tests, other lab tests, and the purchase of medications through the Health Store feature. Any medical recommendations, prescriptions, and diagnoses provided by the Service Provider (doctor) are the medical authority of the respective Service Provider (doctor).
Parenting Feature: The Parenting Feature provides parenting-related information and facilitates Users to consult with Service Providers (doctors) via video call, voice call, or chat accessible through the Halodoc Platform to discuss pregnancy and parenting. This feature also provides lab test services and the purchase of medications through the Health Store feature. Any medical recommendations, prescriptions, and diagnoses provided by the Service Provider (doctor) are the medical authority of the respective Service Provider (doctor).
Immunization Feature: The Immunization Feature provides information about child and adult immunization and facilitates Users to consult with Service Providers (doctors) via video call, voice call, or chat accessible through the Halodoc Platform to discuss the immunizations needed. This feature also provides lab tests, home care or drive-thru vaccination services, and the purchase of medications through the Health Store feature. Any medical recommendations, prescriptions, and diagnoses provided by the Service Provider (doctor) are the medical authority of the respective Service Provider (doctor).
Skin Health Feature: The Skin Health Feature facilitates Users to consult with Service Providers (doctors) via video call, voice call, or chat accessible through the Halodoc Platform to discuss their health. This feature also provides lab test services and the purchase of medications through the Health Store feature. Any medical recommendations, prescriptions, and diagnoses provided by the Service Provider (doctor) are the medical authority of the respective Service Provider (doctor).
My Insurance Feature: Users can link their insurance to the Halodoc Platform to use Services on the Halodoc Platform according to the terms and conditions set by their insurance provider.
Period Tracker Feature: The Period Tracker Feature helps Users track their menstrual cycle to determine ovulation and fertile periods. If necessary, Users can consult with a Service Provider (obstetrician) for further medical assistance.
Pregnancy Tracker Feature: The Pregnancy Tracker Feature helps Users calculate the "estimated due date" and provides information and articles based on the pregnancy stage. If necessary, Users can consult with a Service Provider (obstetrician) for further medical assistance.
BMI Calculator Feature: Users can use the BMI Calculator Feature to calculate their Body Mass Index (BMI). The BMI Calculator Feature does not replace medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment from a doctor.
Medicine Reminder Feature: After Users set a reminder time in the Medicine Reminder Feature, it will help remind Users of their medication schedule.
Diabetes Risk Feature: This interactive feature allows Users to assess their risk of developing diabetes based on personal health information, such as age, weight, and family history. It then provides a risk estimate, enabling Users to take preventive steps or seek medical advice early.
Heart Risk Feature: This feature allows Users to assess their heart health risk, including the risk of a heart attack, based on cardiovascular health information such as cholesterol levels and blood pressure. With personalized risk assessments from this feature, Users can take preventive measures or seek medical advice early.
Donations Feature: Halodoc x Kitabisa, or the Donations Feature, is a fundraising platform that connects donors with health-related campaigns. Through collaboration with Kitabisa, Halodoc provides a space for Users to contribute to supporting medical services and patient treatment, as well as funding various health initiatives under applicable terms and conditions.
Health Protection Feature (Get Insured): Users can purchase health protection provided by Service Providers on the Halodoc Platform according to their needs and subject to the terms and conditions set by the Service Provider.
6.3. Other Services
Subscription Feature
Users can purchase the Doctor Chat Feature Service through the Subscription Feature and check the remaining Services by reviewing their profile under the "Your Healthcare Services" section.
Transaction Terms for the Subscription Feature
This service allows Users to schedule the purchase of healthcare Products that must be consumed within a specific timeframe.
By using the Subscription Service, Users authorize Halodoc to perform auto debit on their GoPay account and/or credit card limit and/or debit card limit registered on the Halodoc Platform to process the payment for the Subscription Service. Users must ensure sufficient funds are available in their GoPay account and/or credit card limit and/or debit card limit registered on the Halodoc Platform at least 3 (three) calendar days before the payment date.
If the balance in the GoPay account and/or credit card limit and/or debit card limit registered on the Halodoc Platform is insufficient, we will send a notification for the User to process the payment so that Halodoc can proceed with the order. If the payment is not completed, the delivery will be marked as "skipped" / "missed."
Halodoc will process the payment 3 (three) calendar days before the delivery of the healthcare Products.
Users may cancel the Subscription Service and/or skip delivery as long as the payment has not been processed. If the payment has been processed, Users can only cancel the next delivery.
Users cannot combine the delivery of other Products with Products purchased through the Subscription Service.
7. INSURANCE
To conduct transactions on the Halodoc Platform, Users utilizing Health Insurance/Health Benefits must link their account with their Health Insurance/Health Benefits. Users can only transact on the Halodoc Platform when their Health Insurance/Health Benefits membership status is active.
Ensure that you have selected the correct profile before using the Doctor Chat Feature.
The Doctor Chat Feature can be used with Healthcare Providers (doctors) marked with a blue label, indicating that they are covered by your Health Insurance/Health Benefits provider.
The Health Store Feature can be used under the terms agreed upon between Halodoc and the Health Insurance/Health Benefits provider, including but not limited to the types of medications and vitamins covered, limitations on medication quantities, and the types of illnesses covered.
The Service Fees set for using the Halodoc Platform are based on agreements with the Health Insurance/Health Benefits provider.
All approved Service Fees will be deducted from your Health Insurance/Health Benefits coverage according to the terms and conditions agreed upon between Halodoc and the Health Insurance/Health Benefits provider.
8. USER TRANSACTIONS
Halodoc Balance
Halodoc Balance is obtained only from refunds for unsuccessful transactions on the Halodoc Platform.
For avoidance of doubt, Halodoc Balance cannot be reloaded.
Users may also withdraw funds through a bank designated by the User if the Halodoc Balance exceeds Rp10,000 (ten thousand Rupiah).
Halodoc Balance cannot be transferred or converted into cash in any form.
Payment Methods
To conduct transactions on the Halodoc Platform, Users can use various payment methods available on the Halodoc Platform. If they have sufficient funds in their Halodoc Balance, Users may use the Halodoc Balance for transactions.
The refund process can be found at this link:
https://www.halodoc.com/faq/questions/berapa-lama-estimasi-pengembalian-dana-refund-halodoc
.
Users agree that Halodoc may suspend any transactions from the User's account if Halodoc detects and/or identifies suspicious transactions, indications of fraud, or other unauthorized transactions based on Halodoc's applicable policies.
Users understand and agree that the maximum time limit for submitting a complaint regarding a transaction is 7 (seven) calendar days after the User’s transaction on the Halodoc Platform has been completed.
