18. ACCOUNT DELETION
You can delete your account by accessing the ‘Delete My Account’ feature available on the Halodoc Platform.
You may also delete a profile created under your account by directly accessing the specific profile you wish to delete.
Depending on the reason for deletion, the information and data associated with the deleted profile will either:
Be permanently deleted; or
Be merged with data stored in other profiles under your account.
Subject to points C and A above, you understand that once your account or any profile created under your account is deleted, your account or any profile created under your account (including all transaction history and all services within it) will be permanently deleted and cannot be recovered by you for any reason.
Your account may be temporarily or permanently suspended for reasons including, but not limited to:
You report that your account has been misused or is suspected of being misused by others;
You report that your phone or tablet has been lost, stolen, or hacked;
Halodoc has reasonable grounds, based on internal policies, to suspect that your account has been transferred or used by someone else;
Halodoc suspects any activity that could harm Halodoc, users, service providers, or other parties;
You have registered or logged into multiple accounts on a single device to violate the Terms and Conditions, Privacy Policy, or applicable Indonesian laws;
Unusual activities are detected on your account, or you have failed to fulfill obligations under the Terms and Conditions and/or Privacy Policy;
The user has passed away, been placed under guardianship, or is legally incapacitated under applicable laws;
Use of the Halodoc Platform or Services in violation of the Terms and Conditions, Privacy Policy, or applicable laws; and/or
An account suspension order, either temporary or permanent, issued by a relevant government or monetary institution, or a court order issued under applicable laws.
If your account is suspended and you have clear evidence that it should not have been suspended, you may submit a report to us along with supporting evidence. Upon further review of your report, we will, at our sole discretion, decide whether to lift or maintain the suspension. Suspensions will not be continued unreasonably if we determine that the issue has been resolved.
