25. APPLICABLE LAW AND DISPUTE RESOLUTION
These Terms and Conditions are governed by the laws and regulations of the Republic of Indonesia.
In the event of a dispute or disagreement arising from or related to the implementation of these Terms and Conditions ("Dispute"), the Parties agree to resolve it through deliberation to reach a consensus or by taking peaceful steps through mutual deliberation upon the emergence of the Dispute.
If the Dispute cannot be resolved through mutual deliberation within 30 (thirty) calendar days from the date the Dispute is notified by one Party to the other, the Parties agree to resolve the Dispute definitively through Arbitration organized by the Indonesian National Arbitration Board ("BANI") in accordance with the prevailing BANI regulations at the time regarding arbitration procedures. The arbitration will be conducted by one (1) arbitrator appointed by the Chairman of BANI and will take place in DKI Jakarta, Indonesia, using the Indonesian language. The arbitration award shall be deemed final, binding, and not subject to appeal, and no Party shall initiate any legal proceedings or file any lawsuit in any court concerning the Dispute arising from or related to these Terms and Conditions.
The Parties agree not to initiate or continue court proceedings regarding any Dispute arising from or related to these Terms and Conditions.
